        <div xml:id="a9cj9a-d1e60">
          <head>Titulus 1</head>
          <head type="question-title">De summa trinitate et fide catholica</head>
            <!-- intro content -->
          <div>
            <head>Capitulum 1</head>
            <p>
              <lb ed="#R"/><quote  type="lemma" source="http://scta.info/resource/cice-l1t1-d1e119@8-8">Firmiter</quote> Non solet summari, sed pro summario diuidi<lb ed="#R"/>tur 
              in duas partes principales. Secunda ibi <quote>Vna ve<lb ed="#R"/>ro</quote>.
              Prima tractat de summa trinitate, &amp; eius operibus
              <lb ed="#R"/>de fide
              <lb ed="#R"/>catho<lb ed="#R"/>lica, 
              &amp; 
              articu<lb ed="#R"/>lis
              fidei. Secunda pars
              <lb ed="#R"/>principalis tractat de sa<lb ed="#R"/>cramentis.
            </p>
            <!-- Casus..; I'm not sure what this is or if it should be included -->
            <p>
              <lb ed="#R"/><quote  type="lemma" source="http://scta.info/resource/cice-l1t1-d1e119@8-8">firmiter</quote> Hoc ideo dicit, quia ordo fidei nostrae probari non potest: &amp; 
              <cb ed="R" n="b"/>
              <lb ed="#R"/>quia ubi ratio deficit fides supplet. <ref target="http://scta.info/resource/gd-p3d4-Dd1e1228"><!-- canon has two sub paragraphs, so target is at canon level -->de conse. di. 4. c. nihil est aliud</ref>; &amp; <ref target="http://scta.info/resource/gd-p3d5-d1e693">dist. 
              vlt. c. vlti.</ref> arg. vt quod sermo sonat, affectus sentiat, id est, fides, <ref target="http://scta.info/resource/gd-p3d2-d1e1134">de conse. dist. 
              <lb ed="#R"/>2. c. reuera, in fi.</ref> quia fides est de re non uisa, <ref target="http://scta.info/resource/gd-p2c33q3d4-d1e227">de poen. dist. 4, in domo, in fi.</ref>
            </p>
            <p>
              <lb ed="#R"/><quote  type="lemma" source="http://scta.info/resource/cice-l1t1-d1e119@9-9">Credimus</quote> Hoc ideo dicit: quia dubius in fide, infidelis est <ref target="http://scta.info/resource/cice-l5t7-d1e119">infra de 
              <lb ed="#R"/>haer. c. 1</ref> &amp; arg. <ref target="http://scta.info/resource/gd-p2c22q1-d1e120">22. q. 1. omne quod. in fi</ref>. Et est simile de accusato con<lb ed="#R"/>tra 
              quem nihil est pro<lb ed="#R"/>batum, &amp; sic remanet du<lb ed="#R"/>bius 
              quando se non purgat. 
              <lb ed="#R"/>Et quia fides est exor<lb ed="#R"/>dium 
              nostrae reparatio<lb ed="#R"/>nis: 
              ideo prius de ea prae<lb ed="#R"/>mittit, 
              quia prius homo 
              <lb ed="#R"/>debet instrui in fide. <ref target="http://scta.info/resource/gd-p3d4-d1e912">de 
              <lb ed="#R"/>conse. distin. 4, ante ba<lb ed="#R"/>ptismum</ref> 
              &amp; <ref target="http://scta.info/resource/gd-p3d4-d1e927">c. ante 20</ref>
            </p>
            <p>
              <quote type="lemma">Simpliciter<!-- this one wasn't in eds doc --></quote>
            </p>
            <p>
              <quote type="lemma">Vnus</quote> hoc dictum fuit ad differentiam plurium planetarum, quos 
              <lb ed="#R"/>quidam colebant tamquam deos.
            </p>
            <p>
              <quote type="lemma">Verus</quote> dictus est ad differentiam fictorum.
            </p>
            <p>
              <quote type="lemma">Aeternus</quote> hoc ideo dicit, quia misericordiae Dei nec mensuras pos<lb ed="#R"/>sumus 
              ponere, nec tempora definire. <ref>de poenae. dist. 1, multiplex</ref>; et <ref>26. q. 6, is qui</ref>.
            </p>
